This is an updated version of the functions developped for the probabilistic hazard assessment of ballistics impacts with the Great Balls of Fire model of Biass et al. (2016):
http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0377027316301317
https://www.researchgate.net/publication/304243833_Great_Balls_of_Fire_A_probabilistic_approach_to_quantify_the_hazard_related_to_ballistics_-_A_case_study_at_La_Fossa_volcano_Vulcano_Island_Italy
https://www.researchgate.net/publication/320005132_Ballistic_hazard_assessment

Details about the method can be found here:
https://e5k.github.io/codes/2017/09/20/ballistic-post-processing/